{"key":"processedPost-13528655","value":{"id":13528655,"first":13488594,"last":13532549,"when":1290527538,"utime":"11/23/10 05:52 PM","cleanedPost":"I think some of you don't realize that the boiling of grains is not to hydrate them.&nbsp; They should be fully hydrated when you boil or they'll burst.&nbsp; Boiling is to heat them up, so they steam dry afterward before loading into jars.&nbsp; This prevents over-wet grain jars which perform poorly if at all.<br />RR"}}